description: Price just dropped to  $189,000 Lady Jasmyn cruises between the US & BVI's & can be viewed in St Croix USVI. Purposely priced low due to the location, the vessel offers great value to prospective buyers for the  investment in an airline ticket. Do not let the location deter you. Come on over and check it out!  The captain/owner can assist buyer on air & affordable lodging on St. Croix as well as easy shipping  or delivery to PR or Florida. Do not miss out on checking out this beautifully maintained yacht. Classic 1985 uniquely designed with an impressive 24' beam. Huge flybridge, cockpit & foredeck for family & friends. New Yanmar engines & gears w/only 400 hours!. Reduced from $295,000 to $219,000 and now just lowered to  $189,000 by motivated owner. She has never been chartered. New bottom paint, zinc's & survey (Feb.2016). The survey was conducted visually & by sounding--"Hulls are in generally good overall condition" (No blisters, de-laminations & issues). Don't let the age fool you. This is a well maintained vintage vessel, far superior to many newer cheaper made vessels that won't hold up like this beauty has over time. This yacht is becoming "timeless" and increasingly more sought after for the purist cruiser. She has never been chartered & properly maintained the value of this boat will not continue to depreciate but will increase. Rock solid and of stout construction she handles heavy sea-ways with ease, safety & comfort.  Professionally installed cost of NEW engines is over $90,000. The pilot-house salon (16' x 16') has an incredible 360 degree panoramic view. Teak & holly soles thru-out. Galley is 10' x 5' w/ 14' of counters. Throughout the interior, rich teak wall coverings & joinery are featured (no plastic). The master & guest forward cabins have walk around queen-sized beds (NO CRAWLING AROUND IN A V-BERTH) .Both aft queen cabins are spacious. The 13'x 20' solid foredeck (w/ 5 huge lockers) is accessed by 2.5' wide walk-arounds. The 9' x 15' cockpit has 26' of continuous cushioned seating shaded by a hard-top/sundeck. The stern has twin 4x5 swim platforms.  The impressive enclosed flybridge has built in cushioned seating for 10 never leaving the Captain out of all the fun. A few specs: Dual Helms,  24'beam, 3.5' draft, 2 X 110 HP turbo diesel Yanmar 4JH4-HTE (new 2012 W/ 400 hrs), 15 KW Westerbeke genset w/ 1950 hrs, 2 Heads, Fuel 400 GAL. Water 200 GAL. A/C thruout. Economical, total for both engines using only 2.8 gals/hr @ cruising speed of 9 knots= 1,400 mile range. Call for inventory. Thanks for looking, Captain Norm. ver datos contacto owner.
